   may assign nonzero proba bility only a subset of labels. We
   intro({''}lice new non-conformity scores for classificaLion that make
   the calibration process correspond to the widely used temperature
   scaling method. At test time, applying; these sparse transformations
   with the calibrated teniper, leads to a support set (i.e., the set of
   zero probability) that automatically inherits the coverage guarantees of
   conformal prediction. Through experiments on computer vision and text
